    "body": "Fast sync only runs the very first time you start geth by default.  After that, you need to add the flag to the command.  I had to jump through some hoops to get geth and the regular GUI java client working together, and outlined my process in the sync issues megathread.  Even with everything seemingly set up perfectly I can't get geth to sync in windows 10 without restarting it multiple times as I outlined in my comment.  I gave up on using anything but the default data dir because both Java client and command line mode only seemed to agree with defaults.  I hope these sync issues are all ironed out over time but for now, it is what it is.  Have you tried a fully default folder and settings sync?  Are you only going to use the console to run geth?  Have you been sure to use the \"geth removedb\" command?",
