    "body": "Re\r\n1. GETH Syncing is quite fast for the first 95% of the blocks and then drops to a halt.\r\n\r\nIt's because first you're fast-synching, after sync to the pivot point it actually process every block/transaction from the pivot point up to the chain head. \r\n\r\n4. When starting the synchronisation process it doesn't seem to start syncing sometimes untill about 5 minutes into the process\r\n\r\nIt's probably searching for suitabe peers at that time. Though I agree that 5  minutes is a bit suspisciously long. \r\n\r\n5. When trying to close the GETH client an error pops up:\r\n\r\nThat one I think is fixed. \r\n\r\n6. Second time running the GETH sync process it won't do a FAST sync anymore\r\n\r\nYep, once you've fast-synced, you will have to sync block by block. The alternative is to wipe the database and do a fast-sync from scratch. ",
